    "word": "Syndicalism",
    "definitions": [
        "The theory, plan, or practice of trade-union action (originally as advocated and practiced by the French Confdirect action including any kind of action that is directly effective, whether it be a simple strike, a peaceful public demonstration, sabotage, or revolutionary violence. By the general strike and direct action syndicalism aims to establish a social system in which the means and processes of production are in the control of local organizations of workers, who are manage them for the common good."
